  />
  <p>
   To facilitate daily activities and movement, indoor layouts must be easy to navigate and comfortable. Therefore, we integrate motion considerations into the design process. For one particular scene, we used motion synthesis and inverse dynamics to evaluate it, followed by optimization with CMA-ES. This approach significantly improved metrics related to human movement distance and energy consumption for grabbing objects. In the future, we aim to refine our metric calculations and incorporate more personalized characteristics into indoor scene design.
  </p>
